NOTES (working — will be removed once design settles)

structure now
  100x100 cartesian grid, 4-connected by default if engine reads it that way
  + outer border (wall, anti-phase like boundary.zc)
  _ between cells horizontally and as full-row dividers
  # at every horizontal-vertical crossing
  cells currently single character (one state-id from LEGEND)
  default state 0 = X (dormant)

reserved by file format (cannot appear as state-id without ambiguity)
  space  (was cell separator before underscore; still avoid)
  +      (border / wall)
  _      (cell separator and divider, was Xv88 in legend)
  #      (intersection marker, was Xv65 in legend)
  newline

open questions for ranadriel
  1 cell payload
      cells are currently single state-id only
      where do the 7 quantum properties (energy phase spin charge coherence coupling observer) live per cell
      options: separate parallel grids per property; nested cell payload; properties live in rana lookup not here
  2 lookup mechanism
      how does state-id at cell (r,c) map to a rana entry
      is the cell value a key into a rana index, or does it route through a sea-specific lookup table
  3 grid topology per sea
      retina is cartesian 4-connected -> fits this template
      brain is amorphous graph -> does not fit grid
      cochlea is 1d tonotopic -> may want a thin grid or a different shape
      nose is glomerular -> graph
      tongue is small region -> small grid
      skin is dermatome 2d -> grid fits
      decision: is template.sea the universal shape, or only the cartesian-grid shape; do graph-shaped seas need a different template
  4 size
      100x100 is arbitrary; per-sea size may vary
      retina should be screen-resolution sized (~2M cells)
      cochlea ~2k cells
      brain 200k+ amorphous nodes
  5 cell-id collisions in legend
      _ and # cannot coexist as both structure and state-id
      either drop them from LEGEND or change file format separators
  6 honeycomb option
      square grid is current default
      hexagonal would change neighbor count from 4 to 6 and require staggered rows
      open: do any seas want hex coupling natively
  7 reading direction
      currently grid is row-major top to bottom, left to right
      does the engine care; does any sea want a different read order

what is settled
  this file is transient state, not code or doctrine
  cells are nodes (sensor/input/output/compute)
  computation is lookup against rana
  outer + border is the wall
